# Code owners for ros2docker.
#
# Changes to the files that define CI, build tooling, packaging, and the
# release pipeline require review from the maintainer. Combined with the
# "require review from Code Owners" ruleset option, this is the owner-vs-
# contributor boundary for the project's automation: a contributor (or an
# agent) cannot silently weaken or rewire CI without explicit owner approval.
#
# Agents (the develNor-agent account) work with full autonomy elsewhere, but
# a PR that touches the paths below needs the owner's Code Owner approval before
# it can merge. This is the only owner gate on the otherwise-autonomous flow,
# plus repo admin and releases. See docs/github-repository-settings.md.

# CI, build tooling, packaging, and policy config.
/.github/                 @develNor
/.pre-commit-config.yaml  @develNor
/pyproject.toml           @develNor
/justfile                 @develNor
/codecov.yml              @develNor

# The contract/policy tests that encode CI and repository invariants.
/tests/contract/          @develNor

# Release pipeline and notes.
/docs/release.md          @develNor
/docs/release-notes/      @develNor
